    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix GTP error indication handling in NGAP interface\n\n### Summary\nThe `Gtpv1uHandleError` function in `gtp_itf.cpp` was not properly implemented, causing NGAP procedure failures between gNB and AMF. The function only logged a message saying \"error handling is missing/not implemented\" and returned an error code, which was causing issues downstream in the NGAP interface handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/ocp-gtpu/gtp_itf.cpp`: Replaced stub implementation with proper error handling according to 3GPP TS 29.281 specification\n  - Parses GTP error indication messages correctly\n  - Extracts TEID that caused the error\n  - Extracts peer IP address if available\n  - Looks up tunnel associated with the failed TEID\n  - Logs appropriate diagnostic information\n  - Returns success to indicate error was handled properly\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen GTP error indications are received from the AMF, they are not properly processed, causing procedure failures in the NGAP interface between gNB and AMF. This can be observed as:\n- NGAP procedure timeouts\n- Failed UE context setup procedures\n- Inability to establish user plane tunnels\n- Error messages in the logs indicating unhandled GTP error indications\n\nThe fix ensures that when GTP error indications are received from the AMF, they are properly processed and don't cause downstream failures in the NGAP interface handling.\n"
}